column5: what the hell... i was doing my christmas shopping at cabelas.com and when i whent to "check out" i was notified that they wouldn't ship sparkle crappie nibbles to canada...? but regular crappie nibles were OK  does anyone know why?  and does anyone know were to get em near ottawa or montreal?
I remember hearing of this before from a buddy... he called and was told that it was "alive" something to do with enzymes?  Randy

I tried to order some jerky mix from them before and when I told them my address they said they can't send that to Canada. Had to do with the food and drug administration or something. Even the guy said that was stupid but that was gov't policy.
very strange and frustrating...guess i'll have to drive to gander mountain in platsburge and SMUGGLE em back...
this sort of thing is actually quite common in other industries, like the pet and fish food industry, for example.  our regulations do not allow some items because of ingredients while the USA does.
Randy, you're getting better looking all the time....
